1. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper deals with large swarms of simple mobile robots, which is a classic problem in multi-agent systems. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper is about controlling micro- and nanorobots, which is a subfield of robotics. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the complexity of motion planning for robot swarms, which is a problem in algorithms and data structures. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with designing systems to control robot swarms, which is a problem in systems and control. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper proves the complexity of finding an optimal control sequence for robot swarms, which is a problem in computational complexity.
